#### Expected behavior

[JvmMetrics](https://github.com/yahoo/pulsar/blob/master/pulsar-broker/src/main/java/com/yahoo/pulsar/broker/stats/metrics/JvmMetrics.java#L67) doesn't return correct `jvm_direct_memory_used`.

#### Actual behavior and Steps to reproduce

```
 @Test
    public void testDirectMemory() throws Exception {

        int pendingMsg = 10_000000;

        PooledByteBufAllocator allocator = new PooledByteBufAllocator( //
                true, // preferDirect
                0, // nHeapArenas,
                1, // nDirectArena
                8192, // pageSize
                11, // maxOrder
                64, // tinyCacheSize
                32, // smallCacheSize
                8 // normalCacheSize
        );
        JvmMetrics jvm = new JvmMetrics(pulsar);
        Field directMemoryUsage = PlatformDependent.class.getDeclaredField("DIRECT_MEMORY_COUNTER");
        directMemoryUsage.setAccessible(true);
        try {
            for (int i = 0; i < pendingMsg * pendingMsg; i++) {
                allocator.directBuffer(10000, 10000);
                if (i % 30000 == 0) {
                    Thread.sleep(1000);
                    System.out.println(i + " used_jdk,used_netty,max :"
                            + jvm.generate().get(0).getMetrics().get("jvm_direct_memory_used") + ",  "
                            + jvm.generate().get(0).getMetrics().get("jvm_max_direct_memory") + ", "
                            + ((AtomicLong) directMemoryUsage.get(null)).get());
                }
            }
        } catch (Throwable th) {
            th.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
```
